OL,3,CThe letter Princess Diana wrote to
OL,4,CAIDS sufferer to boost his spirits
OL,6,FIn 1987, Diana opened the UK's first
OL,7,Fspecialist HIV/AIDS unit at London's
OL,8,FMiddlesex Hospital and notably shook
OL,9,Fthe hand of a man suffering with HIV,
OL,10,Fshowing in a single gesture that the
OL,11,Fcondition needed compassion and
OL,12,Funderstanding, not fear and ignorance.
OL,14,FBobby Warrington from Lay's
OL,15,FAuctioneers in Lanner says the letter
OL,16,Fis "culturally significant" and "shows
OL,17,Fthat Princess Diana really was the
OL,18,FPeople's Princess, because she did it
OL,19,Ffor no other reason apart from to
OL,20,Freach out to someone dying of AIDS".
